{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, when slack variables are high, the problem is deemed infeasible either due to violating the collision constraints or the computational budget being exhausted.",
    "We note that slack variables are commonly used in MPC research to model pareto-optimal solutions.",
    "Overall, the limitations raised by researchers are wide-spread.",
    "Since each production scenario is unique and solutions must be robust due to safety concerns, there is no work that currently solves the general paradigm.",
    "We share our formalization of the general paradigm with Mademlis et al. (2018a), whereby the ideal is a system that can act on a set of highlevel inputs from an operator, who is not required to be technically knowledgeable."
  ]
}